And I could have helped him.

26
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:16,992
That was his own fault.

27
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:19,995
Was it?

28
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:25,334
- What's the matter with you today?
- I'm just a little off my game. I'll get it back.

29
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,710
Rafael!

30
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:29,838
- It felt like she was asking me something.
- That's her son.

31
00:01:29,964 --> 00:01:32,800
She says she knows who killed him,
Some guy named Little Chino.

32
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:35,469
She wants you to find Little Chino
and kill him like a dog.

33
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:37,012
Eva.

34
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:38,806
Are you willing to testify

35
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:42,643
that Little Chino picked up your son
on the night of his death?

36
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:44,311
Come on. Don't back down now.

37
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:48,107
I want him to pay.

38
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:51,276
A challenge, a mountain to climb.

39
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:53,070
I need this one.

40
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:56,824
The scene of the failed crime,
no better place to try again.

41
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:03,831
I don't normally experience failure.

42
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:08,418
39 days, 22 hours and 18 minutes
since I killed my brother.

43
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:10,170
I am cursed.

44
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,673
Two treasure hunters
made a ghastly discovery today

45
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:15,676
when they stumbled on what appears to be
an underwater graveyard

46
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:18,762
in a crevice off the coast of Miami.

47
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:23,350
That means there might be
a new mass murderer out there

48
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,727
way worse than the Ice-Truck Killer.

49
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,643
I'm drifting.

50
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:35,315
I finally get a chance to kill and I can't do it.

51
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:39,945
And a second chance, and he gets away.

52
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:47,953
And now all my secrets
are floating to the surface.

53
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:54,001
Where is the orderly,
controlled, effective Dexter?

54
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,211
How did I lose him?

55
00:04:56,337 --> 00:04:58,422
How do I find him again?

56
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:02,676
I'm drifting...

57
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:07,139
...but not to sleep.

58
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:15,439
...the gruesome discovery
off the coast of Florida yesterday.

59
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:19,568
Police are still searching through evidence
lying at the bottom of the ocean.

60
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:23,864
Sources say there could be multiple victims
in what appears to be the work...

61
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:47,554
Here I am, back in the belly of the beast.

62
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:51,808
But how can I solve a crime when
I can't even solve what's wrong with me?

63
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:55,645
Yet duty calls.

64
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:03,445
Eight confirmed.

65
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:06,782
- Eight confirmed. Here?
- No. Here is just one.

66
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:09,159
Eight confirmed victims
of the Bay Harbor Butcher.

67
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,788
The "Bay Harbor Butcher"?

68
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:16,500
That's what the press is calling
whoever dumped those bodies offshore.

69
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:18,502
Has a nice ring to it, no?

70
00:06:18,628 --> 00:06:20,670
Well, it's a little...

71
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:23,507
- lurid.
- Lurid and possibly wrong.

72
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,968
Part of me is hoping they found
the Ice-Truck Killer's dumping grounds.

73
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:30,222
Tell me about it. The last thing Miami needs is
another serial killer.

74
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:35,060
Eva Arenas. All she wanted was justice

75
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:38,188
against the 29th Street Kings
for whacking her son.

76
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:41,274
- First she's the messenger...
- Now she's a goddamn message.

77
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:46,905
Death by machete. Again.

78
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:51,660
We got a bolo on Little Chino. Gang crash
unit, all local patrols after that cabr?n.

79
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:55,831
Last thing I want is for the cops
to bring Little Chino in.

80
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:57,249
He's mine.

81
00:06:57,375 --> 00:07:00,544
Why don't you take a picture, Morgan?
It'll last longer.

82
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:03,380
